Two accused persons, 22-year-old Sunday Ayeni and Bamidele Awolusi, 27, have been arraigned before an Ado-Ekiti magistrate court, Ekiti State, for allegedly stealing a phone and recharge cards. The police prosecutor, Inspector Olubu Apata, briefed the court yesterday that the defendants committed the offence on October 11, 2019 atÂ  about 12pm at No. 32, Olorunsogo Street, Ado-Ekiti. Inspector Apata alleged that on the said day, the defendants went to the shop of Mrs Janet Fatoba pretending to be interested in buying a padlock but stole one phone valued at N33,500, and a purse containing recharge cards worth N23,500. The prosecutor asked the court for an adjournment to enable him study the case file and assemble his witnesses. Ayeni and Awolusi pleaded not guilty. Their counsel, Mr Gbenga Ariyibi, urged the court to grant them bail, promising they would not jump bail. The magistrate, Mrs Kehinde Awosika, granted the defendants bail in the sum of N50,000, with one surety each in the like sum. Kindly take one minute (1) of your time to fill out this short question. This questionnaire is designed to sample readers' opinions regarding what the feel about Daily Trust newspaper advertisement; it is not intended to used for any purpose other than to improve the quality of our newspapers. Any information provided will therefore be treated as confidential.